Board of Directors
Diliana Alexander
Diliana Alexander serves as the Co-Founder and Executive Director of FilmGate Miami, FilmGate Interactive, and the Downtown Media Center. FilmGate Miami's mission is to cultivate talent and promote innovation within Florida's growing media ecosystem. FilmGate Interactive stands out as one of the premier immersive festivals, taking place during Art Basel Miami. Diliana has produced projects for renowned platforms such as Netflix, HBO, Showtime, PBS, CBC, HGTV, the Learning Channel, and Showtime. Presently, she is directing and producing "Stiltsville VR" for the Oculus Meta platform and programming a monthly dome series for the Frost Science Museum.
​
Nelly Gocheva
Nelly has 15+ years of experience developing media brands and creative strategies within start-ups and legacy brands across North America, Europe and Asia. Through the years, she's held senior positions at Soho House, The New York Times, Monocle Magazine and currently – Apple. Organizations and brands she's worked with on consultancy and brand-marketing partnerships include Nike, Airbnb, LVMH, L’Oréal, Rimowa, Burberry, Chanel, UBS, Credit Suisse, Samsung, BMW, Korean Air, Singapore Tourism Board, the City of Rio de Janeiro, Wunderman Thompson and Diet Coke.
James Powderly
James Powderly is an award-winning technology designer known for inventing tools to empower artists to augment the world. His vision and designs have made a broad cultural and engineering impact with acknowledged contributions in digital art, open source and augmented reality technology. His work can be found in the permanent collection of MoMA, in Snapchat's hardware products and on the surface of Mars. James is the most recent member to join the board at Filmgate Miami. His focus is on identifying and supporting a diverse cohort of creators innovating at the intersection of cryptoart and emerging tech like generative AI and augmented reality.
Billy Corben
Emmy and Peabody Award-winning filmmaker Billy Corben made his feature documentary directorial debut at the Sundance Film Festival in 2001, making him one of the youngest directors in Sundance history. Following that success, he and his producing partners founded Rakontur, a Miami Beach-based content creation company.
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
Lindsay Grace
​
Lindsay is an awarded game designer, developer, author and professor. He is the Knight Chair, Professor and Director of the Master of Fine Arts in Interactive Media at the University of Miami School of Communication. He is Vice President for the Higher Education Video Game Alliance and the 2019 recipient of the Games for Change Vanguard award. Lindsay has curated a variety of international events including The Smithsonian American Art Museum’s SAAM Arcade, the 20th Games for Change Festival, and others. He has authored or co-authored more than 100 books, articles and papers and consults for government and non-profit organizations aiming to employ playful media to solve real word problems.
Lori Wyman
Lori attended the University of Miami and she graduated with her Bachelor's Degree in Speech and Communications and her minor in Education. She received her Master's Degree from Nova Southeastern University (NSU) with a concentration in Drama Therapy. She pursued this degree in order to help actors with Audition Anxiety. Upon graduating with her undergraduate degree, she aggressively pursued a casting career and immediately started working for ACT I Talent Agency. At the time, ACT I was the biggest talent agency in the State of Florida.
Alex Cohen
Alex Cohen is the founder and CEO of Synkronized, a 23 years old US and Global Content Distributor and Production Company. With over 300 Films & Series produced and distributed in the US and worldwide. A library of more than 150 Festival nominations including the Cannes Film Festival, and 52 Awards and counting. Cohen's films have been released in partnership with companies like Paramount, Sony, Lionsgate, and many more. Cohen notably produced Jenna Otega's "Saving Flora" in 2018, Naomie Watts and Octavia Spencer's "Luce", a 2019 Sundance finalist, "Stay Safe" in 2022, and "ODB: Wu-Tang Forever", an upcoming 2023 Series, among dozens of other Productions.
Jose Jacho
Jose Jacho is the co-founder of Filmgate Miami and the Downtown Media Center. He is an out-of-the box thinker and creator, who seeks to establish and maintain South Florida as legitimate location for advancing the arts with the aid of technology.
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
Savannah Niles
Savannah Niles is a multi-disciplinary product and design leader with 9 years in XR. She's currently at Meta, where she leads design for the Quest Core OS. previously, she served as Director of Interaction Design and Product Experience at Magic Leap, where she designed and shipped diverse AR products and holds 20+ patents. An MIT Media Lab graduate, Savannah has crafted interactive experiences for Walt Disney Imagineering and Twitter and has been a SIGGRAPH juror for five years.
Pedro Menocal
Pedro is a legal, business, and strategic advisor with 20 years’ experience representing clients, big and small, from all over the world. He represents both domestic and international clients in a number of industries, primarily private equity, software and technology, media and entertainment, and healthcare.
​
​
​
​
​
​
Jimmy Cheng
Director of International Partnership at Sandman Studios / Sandbox Immersive Festival, and Head of
International Sales at Atlas V / Astrea. Jimmy is focusing on XR distribution, representing contents from
over 170 XR studios, and servicing different
platforms / offline locations to find suitable distribution opportunities. The distribution / licensing model of XR content was immature even until today, which is why Jimmy saw the opportunity to form a solid business model for supporting the creators / studios to distribute their projects and generate reasonable revenue. From November 2018 till today, over US$ 10M royalty fee has
been signed to support the XR ecosystem / licensing model growing more mature.
Meifan Shi
Managing Partner at Waterpoint Lane, a preeminent venture and growth equity firm, drives sustainable transformation in the AgriFoodtech sector. With 18+ years of experience in finance, technology, and value creation, she guides Waterpoint Lane's strategic direction and portfolio. Previously, she pioneered AWS's private equity practice, leading new business verticals, and forging strategic partnerships, overseeing a portfolio exceeding $800 billion AUM. As an investor and board member, she focuses on transformative change for a sustainable future through strategic investments and partnerships with visionary founders. Ms. Shi is also committed to diversity, equity, and inclusion, building a coalition of investors and entrepreneurs united in the mission to create a more equitable world.
Vivian Marthell
Director • Creative • Collaborator • Protogeek • Lizard Whisperer • XR Evangelist • Chile Lover • Medicine Maker • Flow Hacker • Wanderluster • Banned Book Reader • Venturer
*evil laughter*
​​​​
Joanna Popper
Joanna Popper is an award-winning media and technology executive with a strong track record in Hollywood and Silicon Valley, known for launching innovative content and products. Most recently, she was Chief Metaverse Officer at Creative Artists Agency, previously serving as Global Head of XR at HP and EVP of Media & Marketing at Singularity University. Joanna now advises media and tech companies on emerging technologies, including AI and spatial computing, and serves on various boards.
Joel Krieger
Joel is an executive creative leader with over two decades’ of multidisciplinary design experience. Throughout his career, Joel’s work has played at the emergent edge of technology, design, and story.
With one foot in the commercial design world, the other is firmly rooted in regenerative design and development — helping to reimagine our relationship to Earth and to the more-than-human world.

About Us
FilmGate Miami empowers media artists across Florida through education, professional development, and year-round programming in film, immersive storytelling, and creative AI. We champion innovation, diversity, and access—supporting underserved communities and emerging creators. Our mission is to expand Florida’s creative economy through technology-driven arts that educate, inspire, and connect.
As a film organization from Miami, inclusivity and diversity is a fundamental part of what makes us who we are. Our city is a melting pot of different cultures and influences that have inevitably come to define its identity. To deny that in our own organization would undermine everything that makes our city great. This is why IFCM Corp. is committed to developing and maintaining a diverse staff that can bring in all the unique backgrounds and perspectives that make the film world of today such an interesting place to be.
Led by the executive director, Diliana Alexander, and an engaged board, IFCM Corp is committed to a policy of equal employment opportunity and does not discriminate on account of race, age, sexual orientation, place of origin, physical or mental disability, or religious affiliation, or otherwise.
We are committed to maintaining an inclusive, safe, and supportive workplace that is free of any such harassment and discrimination against staff members, volunteers, or agency clients. Harassment or intimidation of a client, staff person, or guest because of that person’s account of race, age, sexual orientation, place of origin, physical or mental disability, or religious affiliation is strictly prohibited and may be grounds for termination. Harassment and intimidation include abusive, foul, or threatening language or behavior and inappropriate and unwelcome comments.

Thank You to Our Sponsors
Thank you to our partners: the Downtown Development Authority, National Endowment of the Arts, Knight Foundation, the Miami-Dade County Department of Cultural Affairs and the Cultural Affairs Council, the Miami-Dade County Mayor and Board of County Commissioners for supporting FilmGate Miami. With their support, we are able to provide educational workshops, engaging events, and valuable resources to empower aspiring filmmakers and storytellers. Their belief in our mission fuels our passion to nurture local talent, foster creativity, and push the boundaries of the Miami film community.

FILMGATE TEAM
Founder & CEO
Diliana Alexander
Diliana Alexander is the co‑founder and Executive Director of FilmGate Miami, FilmGate Interactive, and the Downtown Media Center. A creative and executive producer of both immersive and traditional media, her work includes collaborations with HBO, Netflix, Showtime, HGTV, CBC, and TLC, and international co‑productions with Canada, Spain, and Taiwan. She has served as a speaker and juror at leading festivals such as Tribeca, MUTEK, NewImages, Miami Film Festival, and Kaohsiung Film Festival, and has been a visiting professor at Florida International University and Broward College. Diliana holds an MFA in Film Production and undergraduate degrees in Economics and International Relations from MIUAD, McGill University, and the University of Toronto.

Operations Assistant
Katerina Rivera
Katerina Rivera is FilmGate Miami’s Operations Assistant, proudly representing her Cuban and Puerto Rican roots. Born and raised in Miami, Katerina brings vibrant energy and cultural insight to the team. She plays a key role in coordinating events and volunteers, while also managing FilmGate’s social media presence. FILMGATE TEAM
Founder & CEO
Diliana Alexander
Diliana Alexander is the co‑founder and Executive Director of FilmGate Miami, FilmGate Interactive, and the Downtown Media Center. A creative and executive producer of both immersive and traditional media, her work includes collaborations with HBO, Netflix, Showtime, HGTV, CBC, and TLC, and international co‑productions with Canada, Spain, and Taiwan. She has served as a speaker and juror at leading festivals such as Tribeca, MUTEK, NewImages, Miami Film Festival, and Kaohsiung Film Festival, and has been a visiting professor at Florida International University and Broward College. Diliana holds an MFA in Film Production and undergraduate degrees in Economics and International Relations from MIUAD, McGill University, and the University of Toronto.
